cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the concept of rate-distortion, which is a fundamental concept in information theory (cs.IT). It also uses Kolmogorov complexity, which is a concept related to algorithmic information theory and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the behavior of rate-distortion curves for individual source words, which is related to machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). The paper also explores the notion of low Kolmogorov complexity distortion balls capturing interesting properties of a word, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the different behavior of rate-distortion curves, which is related to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
